---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Icon from '../components/Icon.astro';
const title = "Mapping a cloud estate that outgrew its inventory - Case Study - SubZeroSec";
const description = "Rapid growth had left assets and secrets exposed across a sprawling cloud footprint. Attack surface analysis and OSINT brought the real exposure back under control.";
---
<Base title={title} description={description} active="case-studies">
<section class="phead">
  <div class="phbg" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="index.html">Home</a> <i>/</i> <a href="case-studies.html">Case Studies</a> <i>/</i> <span>Series-C Fintech</span></div><span class="eyebrow">Technology</span>
    <h1>Mapping a cloud estate that outgrew its inventory</h1>
    <p class="lead">Rapid growth had left assets and secrets exposed across a sprawling cloud footprint. Attack surface analysis and OSINT brought the real exposure back under control.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="sec light cutA"><div class="geo" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="wrap"><div class="metrics"><div class="metric"><div class="m">37</div><div class="l">previously unknown assets discovered</div></div><div class="metric"><div class="m">9</div><div class="l">leaked secrets rotated before abuse</div></div><div class="metric"><div class="m">1</div><div class="l">living inventory replacing manual spreadsheets</div></div></div><div class="detail" style="margin-top:2.4rem"><div class="dprose"><h3 class="colh">The challenge</h3><p>The company had scaled from one product to a platform in two years, and its asset inventory had not kept pace. Ahead of an enterprise sales push, it needed to know what it was actually exposing to the internet.</p><h3 class="colh">Our approach</h3><ul class="checks"><li><span class="ck"><Icon name="check" /></span> Discovered and attributed the full external footprint, including forgotten and shadow assets</li><li><span class="ck"><Icon name="check" /></span> Mined public repositories and breach corpora for leaked credentials and secrets</li><li><span class="ck"><Icon name="check" /></span> Identified exposed development environments and over-privileged cloud identities</li><li><span class="ck"><Icon name="check" /></span> Set up continuous monitoring so new exposure surfaces as the estate changes</li></ul></div><aside class="dside"><div class="aside-card"><h4>Sector</h4><p class="asp">Technology</p></div><div class="aside-card"><h4>Services used</h4><div class="relinks"><a href="service-attack-surface-analysis.html">Attack Surface Analysis <Icon name="arrow-right" /></a><a href="service-osint.html">OSINT &amp; Exposure <Icon name="arrow-right" /></a></div></div><a class="btn btn-fill asidebtn" href="contact.html">Start a conversation <Icon name="arrow-right" /></a></aside></div></div></section>
<section class="sec dark"><div class="wrap"><div class="bigquote"><p>&ldquo;They found things we had no record of owning. Now we see new exposure the day it appears instead of during a security review.&rdquo;</p><div class="by">&mdash; VP of Engineering, Series-C Fintech</div></div></div></section>
<section class="sec light cutC"><div class="geo" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="wrap"><div class="cta-in"><span class="eyebrow">Get ahead of zero</span><h2>Ready to see yourself the way an <span class="r">adversary would?</span></h2><p>Book a scoped assessment - we will map what is reachable, prove what is exploitable, and give you a ranked path to closing it before someone finds it first.</p><a href="contact.html" class="btn btn-fill">Book a free scoping call <Icon name="arrow-right" /></a></div></div></section>
</Base>
